1 [(8)] (11) “Net excess generation” means the amount of the electricity
2 generated by an eligible customer–generator that is in excess of the electricity consumed
3 by the eligible customer–generator and that results in a negative kilowatt–hour reading at
4 the end of the eligible customer–generator’s billing cycle.
5 (12) “QUALIFIED SYSTEM” MEANS:
6 (I) A BEHIND–THE–METER ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM
7 ASSOCIATED WITH AN ELIGIBLE CUSTOMER–GENERATOR UNDER THIS SECTION;
8 (II) AN ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM THAT ENGAGES IN METER
9 AGGREGATION UNDER § 7–306.3 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
10 (III) A COMMUNITY SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM.
